• Operating Cash Flow = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -18,924,462.44

Step 2: Identify the current liabilities from the given balance sheet.  
• Current Liabilities = Total Current Liabilities = 1,015,922.54

Step 3: Calculate the Operating Cash Flow to Current Liabilities Ratio using the formula:  
  Ratio = Operating Cash Flow / Current Liabilities  
   = -18,924,462.44 / 1,015,922.54  
   ≈ -18.63

Thus, the operating cash flow to current liabilities ratio is approximately -18.63.
